The paper deals with supervised hashing methods for nearest neighbor search in computer vision applications, which suggests that it belongs to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the challenges of dealing with large and ever-growing datasets, which could fall under information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The proposed method is also online and offers linear complexity, which could be relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) and database (cs.DB) sub-categories.
